sor Generics","text":"","code":"pak::pak(\"r-xla/tengen\")"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/index.html","id":"available-generics","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Available Generics","title":"Tensor Generics","text":"shape(): Different dim() also supporting 0-dimensional tensors. dtype(): Returns data type tensor. as_array(): Converts tensor R array. as_raw(): Converts tensor raw() vector. device(): Returns device tensor. functions: naxes(): Returns number axes tensor. implemented length(shape(x)). nelts(): Returns number elements tensor. implemented prod(shape(x)).","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/index.html","id":"tensor-data-types","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Tensor Data Types","title":"Tensor Generics","text":"tengen provides S3 class hierarchy representing tensor data types via DataType: BooleanType() - Boolean (i1 / pred / bool) IntegerType(bits) - Signed integers (i8, i16, i32, i64) UIntegerType(bits) - Unsigned integers (ui8, ui16, ui32, ui64) FloatType(bits) - Floating point (f32, f64) Utility functions: as_dtype(x): Convert string (e.g. \"f32\") DataType DataType object. is_dtype(x): Check whether object DataType. assert_dtype(x): Assert object DataType. Data types support equality comparison == !=.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/DataType.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"DataType — DataType","title":"DataType — DataType","text":"DataType S3 class representing tensor element type. enum: one singleton object per supported dtype, wrapping canonical dtype string. members element types supported r-xla stack: boolean: bool signed integers: i8, i16, i32, i64 unsigned integers: ui8, ui16, ui32, ui64 floats: f16, bf16, f32, f64 complex: c64, c128 Construct DataType as_dtype(). Inspect dtype_width() is_dtype_float() family predicates.","code":""},{"path":[]},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_array.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"As Array — as_array","title":"As Array — as_array","text":"Convert value (usually tensor framework) R array.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_array.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"As Array — as_array","text":"","code":"as_array(x, ...)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_array.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"As Array — as_array","text":"x () Object. ... () Additional arguments.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_array.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"As Array — as_array","text":"()","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_dtype.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Convert to DataType — as_dtype","title":"Convert to DataType — as_dtype","text":"Convert DataType.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_dtype.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Convert to DataType — as_dtype","text":"","code":"as_dtype(x)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_dtype.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Convert to DataType — as_dtype","text":"x () dtype string (e.g. \"f32\", \"i64\", \"bool\"; aliases \"pred\" \"i1\" map \"bool\") DataType object.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_dtype.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Convert to DataType — as_dtype","text":"DataType","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_raw.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"As Ray — as_raw","title":"As Ray — as_raw","text":"Convert value (usually tensor framework) raw() vector.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_raw.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"As Ray — as_raw","text":"","code":"as_raw(x, ...)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_raw.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"As Ray — as_raw","text":"x () Object. ... () Additional arguments.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/as_raw.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"As Ray — as_raw","text":"()","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/assert_dtype.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Assert DataType — assert_dtype","title":"Assert DataType — assert_dtype","text":"Assert object DataType.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/assert_dtype.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Assert DataType — assert_dtype","text":"","code":"assert_dtype(x, arg = rlang::caller_arg(x))"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/assert_dtype.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Assert DataType — assert_dtype","text":"x () Object check. arg (character(1)) Argument name error messages.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/assert_dtype.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Assert DataType — assert_dtype","text":"NULL (invisibly). Called side effects.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/device.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Device — device","title":"Device — device","text":"Get device tensor.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/device.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Device — device","text":"","code":"device(x, ...)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/device.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Device — device","text":"x () Object. ... () Additional arguments.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/device.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Device — device","text":"()","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Data Type — dtype","title":"Data Type — dtype","text":"Get data type tensor. return type depends specific tensor implementation.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Data Type — dtype","text":"","code":"dtype(x, ...)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Data Type — dtype","text":"x () Object. ... () Additional arguments.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Data Type — dtype","text":"()","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype_category.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Category of a DataType — dtype_category","title":"Category of a DataType — dtype_category","text":"category DataType: one \"bool\", \"int\", \"uint\", \"float\", \"complex\".","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype_category.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Category of a DataType — dtype_category","text":"","code":"dtype_category(x)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype_category.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Category of a DataType — dtype_category","text":"x (DataType)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype_category.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Category of a DataType — dtype_category","text":"character(1)","code":""},{"path":[]},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype_width.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Width of a DataType — dtype_width","title":"Width of a DataType — dtype_width","text":"width bits one element given DataType. bool 1; complex types total width element (c64 -> 64).","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype_width.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Width of a DataType — dtype_width","text":"","code":"dtype_width(x)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype_width.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Width of a DataType — dtype_width","text":"x (DataType)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/dtype_width.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Width of a DataType — dtype_width","text":"integer(1)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/is_dtype.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Is DataType — is_dtype","title":"Is DataType — is_dtype","text":"Check object DataType.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/is_dtype.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Is DataType — is_dtype","text":"","code":"is_dtype(x)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/is_dtype.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Is DataType — is_dtype","text":"x () Object check.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/is_dtype.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Is DataType — is_dtype","text":"logical(1)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/is_dtype_float.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"DataType Category Predicates — is_dtype_float","title":"DataType Category Predicates — is_dtype_float","text":"Check category DataType belongs : is_dtype_float(): floating point, including bf16. is_dtype_int(): signed integers. is_dtype_uint(): unsigned integers. is_dtype_bool(): bool. is_dtype_complex(): c64, c128.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/is_dtype_float.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"DataType Category Predicates — is_dtype_float","text":"","code":"is_dtype_float(x)  is_dtype_int(x)  is_dtype_uint(x)  is_dtype_bool(x)  is_dtype_complex(x)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/is_dtype_float.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"DataType Category Predicates — is_dtype_float","text":"x (DataType)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/is_dtype_float.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"DataType Category Predicates — is_dtype_float","text":"logical(1)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/naxes.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Number of Axes — naxes","title":"Number of Axes — naxes","text":"Get number axes tensor.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/naxes.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Number of Axes — naxes","text":"","code":"naxes(x)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/naxes.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Number of Axes — naxes","text":"x () Object.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/naxes.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Number of Axes — naxes","text":"(integer)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/nelts.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Number of Elements — nelts","title":"Number of Elements — nelts","text":"Get number elements tensor.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/nelts.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Number of Elements — nelts","text":"","code":"nelts(x)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/nelts.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Number of Elements — nelts","text":"x () Object.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/nelts.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Number of Elements — nelts","text":"(integer)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/shape.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Shape — shape","title":"Shape — shape","text":"Get shape tensor.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/shape.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Shape — shape","text":"","code":"shape(x, ...)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/shape.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Shape — shape","text":"x () Object. ... () Additional arguments.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/shape.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Shape — shape","text":"(integer()) shape tensor.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/news/index.html","id":"tengen-development-version","dir":"Changelog","previous_headings":"","what":"tengen (development version)","title":"tengen (development version)","text":"breaking: DataType hierarchy (BooleanType(), IntegerType(), UIntegerType(), FloatType()) replaced single enum-style DataType (adds f16, bf16, c64/c128). Construct dtypes as_dtype(). new: dtype_width(), is_dtype_float(), is_dtype_int(), is_dtype_uint(), is_dtype_bool(), is_dtype_complex(). Renamed ndims() naxes(). Added axes() returning axis indices tensor, .e. seq_len(naxes(x)).","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/news/index.html","id":"tengen-020","dir":"Changelog","previous_headings":"","what":"tengen 0.2.0","title":"tengen 0.2.0","text":"Added DataType class hierarchy: BooleanType, IntegerType, UIntegerType, FloatType ==/!= comparison, print(), .character() methods. Added as_dtype() generic convert strings (e.g. \"i32\", \"f64\") DataType objects. Added is_dtype() assert_dtype() helpers type checking. Added nelts() generic get number elements tensor. Renamed TensorDataType DataType.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/news/index.html","id":"tengen-010","dir":"Changelog","previous_headings":"","what":"tengen 0.1.0","title":"tengen 0.1.0","text":"Initial release r-universe","code":""}]
